    "body": "### Problem\n\nBengali text is not supported well in Neovim, some progress has been made in this regard in issues [#29147](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/29147) and [#13623](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/13623). As pointed out before, this is an issue of consonant constructs. I have verified this on this [list](https://github.com/lifeparticle/Bengali-Alphabet#user-content-consonant-conjuncts-%E0%A6%AF%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B7%E0%A6%B0), it reproduces them correctly. But there are still a few problems, which I have listed below:\n\n1. The spacing around the punctuation seems to be a bit off.  \n 1.1 It introduces extra spaces before the comma.\n  1.2 The line breaks are not preserved.\n2. Also, for the text objects are not consistent. \n 2. \"w\" or \"e\" doesn't move to the word end, it stops at the middle of a word. \n 3. The h, j, k, l navigation seems to be broken.\n \n### Software details\n```NVIM v0.12.0-dev-849+gfd5d04fbff\nBuild type: RelWithDebInfo\nLuaJIT 2.1.1744317938\n```\n\nrun with \n\n```\nnvim-linux-x86_64.appimage --clean\n```\n\non Konsole with hamburger menu>edit current profile> appearance> complex text layout> Brahmic scripts characters. \n\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nHere is a [sample_text.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21322085/sample_text.txt) file. And it should be rendered like\n<img width=\"1901\" height=\"626\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/218340f4-17c0-491a-b246-f8191d354e79\" />",
